==English==
===Etymology===
Modern Latin, named after English naturalist Adam Buddle (d. 1715).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈbʌdlɪə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[tree]] or [[shrub]] of the genus ''Buddleja'', especially ''Buddleja davidii'', a large ornamental shrub whose lilac flowers attract [[butterflies]].

====Synonyms====
*[[butterfly bush]]